                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c51rC7p",
                    "body": "I think slightly better as\r\n```suggestion\r\n  DFinsupp.mapRange.linearMap f\r\n```",
                    "createdAt": "2025-02-27T19:29:18Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "eric-wieser"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c51rDFv",
                    "body": "Notably this removes the need for the `DecidableEq` arguments.",
                    "createdAt": "2025-02-27T19:29:53Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "eric-wieser"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c51wTNQ",
                    "body": "presumably Eric meant:\r\n```suggestion\r\n  DFinsupp.mapRange.addMonoidHom f\r\n```\r\nin which case the proof of `map_of` can be fixed with:\r\n```lean\r\n  show DFinsupp.mapRange.addMonoidHom f (DFinsupp.single i x) = DFinsupp.single i (f i x) \r\n  simp\r\n```",
                    "createdAt": "2025-02-28T15:24:51Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "j-loreaux"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c51wYVS",
                    "body": "There should be a single lemma you can invoke for that too.\r\n\r\nThis of course raises the question of whether we want a linearMap-valued `map` in addition to the `AddMonoidHom`-valued one.",
                    "createdAt": "2025-02-28T15:36:58Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "eric-wieser"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c51wIA9",
                    "body": "This is what the `congr()` term elaborator is useful for.\r\n```suggestion\r\n    simpa using congr($(h) i)\r\n```",
                    "createdAt": "2025-02-28T14:55:48Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "j-loreaux"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c51zVqH",
                    "body": "Thanks for the suggestion! I never realized there's such a term elaborator before!",
                    "createdAt": "2025-03-01T11:42:21Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "xyzw12345"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c51wMYw",
                    "body": "I realize this is longer, but I think it better reflects Mathlib style. We generally avoid putting several tactics on one line, even if they manage to fit. Sometimes people do two, but almost never 3 or 4. Also, it's nice to use the `induction` tactic, and the `rfl` in the `obtain` / `rcases` pattern syntax.\r\n```suggestion\r\n  induction x using DirectSum.induction_on with\r\n  | H_zero => exact ⟨0, by simp⟩\r\n  | H_basic i x =>\r\n    obtain ⟨y, rfl⟩ := h i x\r\n    exact ⟨of α i y, by simp⟩\r\n  | H_plus x y hx hy => \r\n    obtain ⟨u, rfl⟩ := hx\r\n    obtain ⟨v, rfl⟩ := hy\r\n    exact ⟨u + v, by simp⟩\r\n```",
                    "createdAt": "2025-02-28T15:07:23Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "j-loreaux"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c51wOU7",
                    "body": "```suggestion\r\n  induction x using DirectSum.induction_on with\r\n  | H_zero => simp\r\n  | H_basic j x =>\r\n    obtain rfl | h := eq_or_ne j i\r\n    · simp\r\n    · simp [of_apply, h]\r\n  | H_plus x y hx hy => simp [hx, hy]\r\n```",
                    "createdAt": "2025-02-28T15:12:33Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "j-loreaux"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
